  6. public SwerveSubsystem(File directory)
    7.

    8. 
          
  8.   // Angle conversion factor is 360 / (GEAR RATIO * ENCODER RESOLUTION)
    9. 
          
  9.   //  In this case the gear ratio is 12.8 motor revolutions per wheel rotation.
    10. 
          
  10.   //  The encoder resolution per motor revolution is 1 per motor revolution.
    11. 
          
  11.   double angleConversionFactor = SwerveMath.calculateDegreesPerSteeringRotation(12.8, 1);
    12. 
          
  12.   // Motor conversion factor is (PI * WHEEL DIAMETER IN METERS) / (GEAR RATIO * ENCODER RESOLUTION).
    13. 
          
  13.   //  In this case the wheel diameter is 4 inches, which must be converted to meters to get meters/second.
    14. 
          
  14.   //  The gear ratio is 6.75 motor revolutions per wheel rotation.
    15. 
          
  15.   //  The encoder resolution per motor revolution is 1 per motor revolution.
    16. 
          
  16.   double driveConversionFactor = SwerveMath.calculateMetersPerRotation(Units.inchesToMeters(4), 6.75, 1);
    17. 
          
  17.   System.out.println("\"conversionFactor\": {");
    18.

    19.

    20.
